.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-344-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-345-1. Source spec packet `decision-record.md` and `implementation-summary.md` are authoritative.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:346:2. Skill-local `benchmark-report.md` is the curated operator-facing summary.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-347-3. Copied CSV and JSONL files preserve the source packet evidence.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-348-4. `source.md` is navigation, not a duplicate audit trail.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-349-
--
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-360-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-361-1. Never promote an in-flight benchmark as a final skill-local record.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-362-2. Never compare numeric results across different MCP stacks as if equivalent.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:363:3. Never paste the full spec packet audit trail into `benchmark-report.md`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-364-4. Never create a new dated folder for a confirming re-run.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-365-5. Never name the folder by authoring date, source packet slug, or candidate name.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-366-6. Never leave template placeholders in shipped benchmark files.
