.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md-146-
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:147:- **SC-001**: A newly generated parent hub contains the same compiled-routing directive shape as the seven established hubs, with its own hub name rendered in the command and fallback sentence.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:148:- **SC-002**: `legacy` generation emits no manifest and is reported as legacy by construction.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:149:- **SC-003**: `ready` generation is reported as compiled-ready only after the canonical manifest exists and the shared predicate confirms freshness.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:150:- **SC-004**: A mint or freshness failure cannot be mistaken for compiled-ready output.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md-151-- **SC-005**: Existing parent and standalone generation invocations retain backward-compatible behavior.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:152:- **SC-006**: The implementation adds no local eligibility list and edits no frozen scorer file.
