.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md-32-| Lane | Pick when | Command |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md-33-| --- | --- | --- |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md-34-| **Lane A: Agent-Improvement** | You want to improve a bounded agent `.md` file | `/deep:agent-improvement` |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md:35:| **Lane B: Model-Benchmark** | You want to benchmark a model or prompt framework | `/deep:model-benchmark` |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md:36:| **Lane C: Skill-Benchmark** | You want to diagnose a skill's real-world routing, discovery, efficiency, and usefulness | `/deep:skill-benchmark` |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md-37-
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md:38:Lane A is detailed in §3 (Runtime Initialization, Proposal and Evaluation, Promotion and Recovery). Lane B is detailed in §4. Lane C (skill-benchmark) is documented in `references/skill-benchmark/` (operator guide, scoring contract, scenario authoring) and run via `loop-host.cjs --mode=skill-benchmark`. All lanes run the same loop shape and keep the agent-improvement path byte-identical when no mode flag is set.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md-39-
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md-40-### Activation Triggers
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md-41-
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md-42-Use this skill when:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md-43-- You want to test whether an agent prompt or instruction surface can be improved (Lane A)
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md:44:- You want to benchmark a model or prompt framework against repeatable fixtures (Lane B)
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md:45:- You want to diagnose whether a skill is well-routed, discoverable, efficient, and useful in practice (Lane C)
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md-46-- The mutation boundary is explicit and narrow
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md-47-- You need packet-local evidence instead of ad hoc prompt tweaking
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md-48-- You need target-specific benchmark or scoring rules before any canonical mutation
--
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md-51-### Primary Use Cases
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md-52-
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md-53-- **Lane A** — proposal-first loop for any bounded agent file: packet-local candidates, dynamic 5-dimension scoring, append-only evidence, guarded promotion/rollback with drift review kept separate. See §3.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md:54:- **Lane B** — benchmarks a model or prompt framework (not an agent file) against a benchmark profile, scoring produced outputs; shares the candidate, dispatcher, and scorer seams with Lane A. See §4.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md:55:- **Lane C** — diagnoses whether a *skill* is well-routed, discoverable, efficient, and useful in practice; emits a ranked Skill Benchmark Report and is diagnostic by default (no target mutation). See `references/skill-benchmark/operator-guide.md`.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md-56-
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md-57-### When NOT to Use
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md-58-
--
