.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md-143-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md:144:**`skill-benchmark-report.md` is a machine render. Never hand-author or hand-edit
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md-145-it.** It is produced solely by the deep-improvement renderer
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md:146:[`build-report.cjs`](../../../../system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/build-report.cjs),
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md:147:which renders the Markdown FROM `skill-benchmark-report.json` specifically so the
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md:148:two artifacts cannot drift. That renderer is the ONLY writer of the report `.md`;
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md:149:it takes the report object, not score arguments.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md-150-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md-151-The consequences of this boundary:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md-152-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md-153-| Rule | Why |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md-154-| --- | --- |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md:155:| Do not edit `skill-benchmark-report.md` by hand | It is an anti-drift render of the JSON. A hand edit desynchronizes it from its source of truth and is silently overwritten on the next run. |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md:156:| Do not author a fill-in template for `skill-benchmark-report.md` | There is no authoring template for a rendered report. To change the report, change the JSON the run emits or the renderer, both owned by deep-improvement. Templates in this packet are for the hub `benchmark/README.md` index and for INPUT fixtures/profiles only. |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md-157-| Do not copy the D1-D5 scoring, reviewer schema, or any scorer/runner into this packet | The scoring contract, reviewer schema, and the runner/renderer scripts are lane-local to deep-improvement. Cross-link them; never relocate them. |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md-158-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md:159:To correct a report: fix the input (fixtures/router/scenario gold) or the scorer,
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md:160:then re-run Lane C so the renderer regenerates the pair. Never patch the `.md`.
