.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/README.md-12-
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/README.md-13----
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/README.md-14-
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/README.md-15-## 1. OVERVIEW
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/README.md-16-
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/README.md:17:`skill-benchmark/` owns the Lane C (skill-benchmark) executables: benchmark a target skill's live routing, discovery, efficiency, and usefulness against its own authored `manual_testing_playbook`, then score the result on five dimensions and render a dual machine/human report. Private gold never crosses the dispatch boundary — scenarios are dispatched on a public prompt and joined back to gold only at scoring time.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/README.md-18-
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/README.md-19-Current state:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/README.md-20-
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/README.md:21:- `run-skill-benchmark.cjs` is the orchestrator (`loop-host --mode=skill-benchmark`). It runs the D5 connectivity hard gate FIRST, loads playbook scenarios into gold, dispatches per scenario, aggregates, and writes `report.json` then renders `report.md` from it.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/README.md:22:- Three executors back the scenarios: `router-replay.cjs` (Mode A deterministic), `live-executor.cjs` (Mode B `cli-opencode`), and `browser-executor.cjs` (`bdg`). `executor-dispatch.cjs` is the seam that routes by `classKind` + trace mode and normalizes every executor into one observed-result shape.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/README.md:23:- `score-skill-benchmark.cjs` computes the D1-D5 dimensions per scenario and aggregates with point weights; Mode A normalizes over only the dimensions it can measure rather than faking the live-only ones. It also carries the advisory `D4_task_outcome` signal.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/README.md-24-- `d4-ablation.cjs` holds the D4 hallucination ablation AND the opt-in `--d4` D4-R task-outcome ablation (advisory `D4_task_outcome`, never collapsed into D4).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/README.md-25-- Supporting modules: `contamination-lint.cjs` (pre-dispatch hint-free gate), `advisor-probe.cjs` (D1-inter advisor signal), `playbook-generator.cjs` (opt-in staged scenario generator), and `_args.cjs` (space-form arg parser). `load-playbook-scenarios.cjs` is the corpus loader.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/README.md-26-
--
