     9	
    10	# sk-code Skill-Benchmark Artifacts
    11	
    12	> Reports and inputs for benchmarking how well `sk-code` is routed, discovered, and used in practice, kept beside the skill they measure.
    13	
    14	---
    15	
    16	## 1. OVERVIEW
    17	
    18	The deep-improvement Lane C harness benchmarks `sk-code` against its own `manual_testing_playbook` scenarios across five dimensions (D1 routing, D2 discovery, D3 efficiency, D4 usefulness, D5 connectivity). This folder holds the run inputs and the dual reports each run writes.
    19	
    20	Two trace modes score the same playbook corpus:
    21	
    22	- **router** is deterministic and offline. For a hub skill it replays `hub-router.json` + `mode-registry.json`; for a flat skill it replays the machine-readable router in `sk-code/shared/references/smart-routing.md`. This is the CI gate.
    23	- **live** dispatches each scenario through `cli-opencode` to a real model and grades the model's stated routing plus observed activation. This is the operator default for a true routing verdict.
    24	
    25	### Key Statistics
    26	
    27	| Metric | Value |
    28	|---|---|
    29	| Corpus | sk-code `manual_testing_playbook` (28 deterministic scenarios across 8 categories, including `DR-001`..`DR-004`) |
    30	| Trace modes | router (deterministic CI gate), live (real dispatch) |
    31	| Latest router verdict | PASS, aggregate 84/100 (`router_final`) |
    32	| Latest live verdict | CONDITIONAL, aggregate 71/100 (`live_final`) |
    33	| D4 usefulness (approximate) | about 49 |
    34	
    35	### How This Compares
    36	
    37	| Tool | Checks | Use When |
    38	|---|---|---|
    39	| This benchmark | Whether the skill is routed, discovered, and useful in practice | Measuring real routing quality |
    40	| `validate.sh` | Document shape and required sections | Checking spec-folder structure |
    41	| `manual_testing_playbook` | Described behavior per scenario | Authoring or hand-running scenarios |
    42	
    43	---
    44	
    45	## 2. QUICK START
    46	
    47	Run from the repository root.
    48	
    49	Router mode (deterministic, no network):
    50	
    51	```bash
    52	node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs \
    53	  --mode=skill-benchmark --skill=sk-code \
    54	  --outputs-dir=.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/router-final \
    55	  --trace-mode=router
    56	```
    57	
    58	Live mode (dispatches through cli-opencode, needs a configured provider):
    59	
    60	```bash
    61	SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_MODEL=openai/gpt-5.5-fast SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_VARIANT=high \
    62	node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs \
    63	  --mode=skill-benchmark --skill=sk-code \
    64	  --outputs-dir=.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/live-final \
    65	  --trace-mode=live --advisor-mode=python \
    66	  --scenarios=SD-001,LS-001,CS-001,RD-002,MR-001
    67	```
    68	
    69	Expected result: a `verdict=` line on stdout plus `skill-benchmark-report.json` and `skill-benchmark-report.md` in the outputs dir.
    70	
    71	---
    72	
    73	## 3. STRUCTURE
    74	
    75	```text
    76	benchmark/
    77	+-- router-final/      # Current deterministic run (router mode)
    78	+-- live-final/        # Current live run (cli-opencode) + d4-ablation.json
    79	+-- baseline/          # Frozen pre-optimization snapshot, do not regenerate
    80	+-- after/ full/ live/ # Earlier development runs, superseded by the -final pair
    81	`-- fixtures/sk-code/   # Legacy synthetic fixtures, superseded by the playbook corpus
    82	```
    83	
    84	| Path | Purpose |
    85	|---|---|
    86	| `router-final/` | Latest router-mode report (real-gold scoring, the CI gate) |
    87	| `live-final/` | Latest live-mode report plus `d4-ablation.json` (skill-on vs skill-off usefulness) |
    88	| `baseline/` | First sk-code run, kept as a before-snapshot, not reproducible |
    89	| `fixtures/sk-code/` | Two legacy fixtures, no longer the default corpus |
    90	
    91	### Run-Label Index
    92	
    93	Every run-label folder on disk, one row each. `Status` separates current runs from legacy sidecars: `current` is a canonical run the sections above point at, `superseded` is an earlier development run kept only as evidence, `frozen` is the immutable before-anchor, `sidecar` is an additional run kept beside the canonical pair, and `legacy` is a pre-playbook artifact. Underscore-named folders are listed exactly as they sit on disk; the hyphenated display names in the tree above (`router-final`, `live-final`, `fixtures/sk-code`) refer to the same `router-final/`, `live-final/`, and `fixtures/sk-code/` folders. Verdicts are read from each folder's report.
    94	
    95	| Run label | What it is | Verdict | Status |
    96	|---|---|---|---|
    97	| [`router-final/`](./router-final/) | Current router-mode run (the deterministic CI gate) | PASS · 84 | current |
    98	| [`live-final/`](./live-final/) | Current live-mode run (`cli-opencode` dispatch) | CONDITIONAL · 71 | current |
    99	| [`d4r-live/`](./d4r-live/) | D4-R task-outcome usefulness ablation, advisory only (see its own `README.md`) | PASS · 88 (base-live) | current · advisory |
   100	| [`router-baseline/`](./router-baseline/) | Router-mode sidecar run | PASS · 85 | sidecar |
   101	| [`live-mode-b/`](./live-mode-b/) | Live-mode (Mode B) sidecar run | CONDITIONAL · 66 | sidecar |
   102	| [`live-remediated/`](./live-remediated/) | Live-mode run after a remediation pass, an intermediate before `live-final/` | CONDITIONAL · 79 | superseded |
   103	| [`baseline/`](./baseline/) | Frozen pre-optimization snapshot; the D5 structural gate blocked this run | BLOCKED-BY-STRUCTURE | frozen |
   104	| [`after/`](./after/) | Earlier router-mode development run | CONDITIONAL · 69 | superseded |
   105	| [`full/`](./full/) | Earlier router-mode development run (full corpus) | CONDITIONAL · 55 | superseded |
   106	| [`live/`](./live/) | Earlier live-mode development run | CONDITIONAL · 76 | superseded |
   107	| [`fixtures/sk-code/`](./fixtures/sk-code/) | Legacy synthetic fixtures, superseded by the playbook corpus | n/a — see folder | legacy |
   108	
   109	---
   110	
   111	## 4. READING THE REPORTS
   112	
   113	Each run writes a matched pair:
   114	
   115	| File | Content |
   116	|---|---|
   117	| `skill-benchmark-report.json` | Machine report: verdict, D1 to D5, funnel, ranked bottlenecks, scenario rows |
   118	| `skill-benchmark-report.md` | The same report rendered for reading, generated from the JSON to avoid drift |
   119	| `d4-ablation.json` | Usefulness deltas per scenario (skill-on score, skill-off score), stamped approximate |
   120	
   121	Start with the `.md` file for the verdict and the ranked bottlenecks. Open the `.json` file for per-scenario detail.
   122	
   123	---
   124	
   125	## 5. TROUBLESHOOTING
   126	
   127	| What you see | Cause | Fix |
   128	|---|---|---|
   129	| Live dispatch returns null after about 4 minutes | `xhigh` reasoning variant is too slow per dispatch | Set `SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_VARIANT=high` |
   130	| `provider/model not found` or 401 in live mode | The provider is not configured | Run `opencode providers list`, then log in to the provider you name in `SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_MODEL` |
   131	| Browser scenarios skip with `SKIP-NO-BROWSER` | `bdg` (Chrome) is unavailable | Install `bdg`, or accept the honest skip for non-Chrome legs |
   132	| Router mode reports orphan references | A routable doc is not reachable from the router | Add it to `RESOURCE_MAP` or the always-loaded default in `smart-routing.md` |
   133	
   134	---
   135	
   136	## 6. RELATED RESOURCES
   137	
   138	### Related Skills
   139	
   140	| Skill | Relationship | Use When |
   141	|---|---|---|
   142	| [`deep-improvement`](../../system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/SKILL.md) | Owns the Lane C benchmark harness | Running or extending the benchmark |
   143	| [`sk-code`](../SKILL.md) | The skill under measurement | Reading or tuning the router being scored |
   144	
   145	### Related Documents
   146	
   147	| Document | Purpose |
   148	|---|---|
   149	| [`smart-routing.md`](../shared/references/smart-routing.md) | The machine-readable router the benchmark replays for a flat skill (a hub replays `hub-router.json`) |
   150	| [`/deep:skill-benchmark`](../../../commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md) | The command that drives a benchmark run |
   151	| [`sk-doc/create-benchmark`](../../sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md) | Authoring templates for this `benchmark/README.md` index + the run-label storage standard (§10: [`skill-benchmark-readme-template.md`](../../sk-doc/create-benchmark/assets/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-readme-template.md), [`skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md`](../../sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md)); the per-run `skill-benchmark-report.md` stays renderer-owned |

