.opencode/commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md-1----
.opencode/commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md-2-description: "Benchmark a skill's real-world routing, discovery, efficiency, and usefulness (Lane C). Emits a ranked, remediable Skill Benchmark Report. Modes :auto, :confirm."
.opencode/commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md:3:argument-hint: "<skill_id_or_root> [:auto|:confirm] [--outputs-dir=PATH] [--fixtures-dir=PATH] [--trace-mode=router|live] [--advisor-mode=python]"
.opencode/commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md-4-allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task
.opencode/commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md-5-skill: system-deep-loop
.opencode/commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md-6----
.opencode/commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md-7-
--
.opencode/commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md-10-Lane C of the `deep-improvement` skill. Benchmarks whether a **skill** is well-structured, well-routed, efficient, and useful **in practice** — how AIs actually discover and use it — and emits a ranked Skill Benchmark Report with concrete, remediable findings. Distinct from `sk-doc`/`validate.sh` (doc shape) and manual testing playbooks (described behavior).
.opencode/commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md-11-
.opencode/commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md-12-## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT
.opencode/commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md-13-
.opencode/commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md:14:Thin router for the skill-benchmark loop. This command verifies the runtime agent, resolves setup and execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML. Scoring, contamination-lint, router-replay, and report rendering are owned by the loop-host scripts and the workflow YAML — never inline in this document.
.opencode/commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md-15-
.opencode/commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md-16-Load the presentation contract before showing startup questions, resolved-input confirmations, result output, failure output, or next-step prompts.
.opencode/commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md-17-
