.opencode/commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md-98-1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for attached suffixes: `:auto` sets `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS`; `:confirm` sets `execution_mode = INTERACTIVE`; no suffix sets `execution_mode = ASK`.
.opencode/commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md:99:2. Treat the skill id/root, `--outputs-dir`, `--fixtures-dir`, `--trace-mode`, and `--advisor-mode` as workflow inputs, not execution modes.
.opencode/commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md-100-3. Resolve the Mandatory Input Gate values from `$ARGUMENTS` and defaults. For `:auto`, resolve confidently or fail fast naming the missing inputs; for `:confirm`/no suffix, present the resolved inputs and wait for confirmation.
.opencode/commands/deep/skill-benchmark.md-101-4. After Phase 0 and the input gate pass, read the target skill's SKILL.md + the operator guide, then load the matching workflow YAML in §4 and execute it step by step using the resolved setup values.
