    24	<!-- ANCHOR:summary -->
    25	## 1. SUMMARY
    26	
    27	### Technical Context
    28	
    29	| Aspect | Value |
    30	|--------|-------|
    31	| **Language/Stack** | Node.js/CommonJS harness plus Vitest |
    32	| **Legacy observation** | Frozen `router-replay.cjs` Mode A output |
    33	| **Compiled observation** | Public `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` child process with flag `1` |
    34	| **Gold evaluator** | Frozen `evaluateRouteGold()` export |
    35	| **Report authority** | `report.json`, with Markdown rendered by `build-report.cjs` |
    36	| **Mutation posture** | Read-only diagnostics; no manifest mint or routing-input write |
    37	
    38	### Overview
    39	
    40	Add one new parity module at the orchestrator boundary. It hashes the frozen files, asks the shared eligibility/status interface what compiled outcome is expected, obtains legacy and compiled observations, normalizes them, and evaluates both against the existing route gold. The orchestrator adds structured parity results and a distinct gate; the scorer and scenario loader remain unchanged.
    41	
    42	This design keeps responsibilities clean: existing files continue to define legacy replay and scoring, while the new harness proves the served compiled path matches them.
    43	<!-- /ANCHOR:summary -->
    44	
