.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/operator-guide.md-19-
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/operator-guide.md-20-## 1. OVERVIEW
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/operator-guide.md-21-
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/operator-guide.md:22:Run Lane C with `loop-host.cjs --mode=skill-benchmark` (or `/deep:skill-benchmark`). The orchestrator runs the D5 structural hard gate first, then per-scenario contamination-lint → router-replay → score, then writes a dual JSON+Markdown report. Mode A is deterministic and is the CI gate; the D1-inter advisor probe, the live trace (Mode B), and the D4-R task-outcome ablation are all opt-in (live/paid), kept off the CI path.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/operator-guide.md-23-
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/operator-guide.md-24-> **Mode B (live playbook) — BUILT** (packet `122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/010-skill-benchmark-live-playbook-mode`). Beyond the synthetic-fixture Mode A above, Lane C can now use a skill's own `manual_testing_playbook` as the corpus and score it in two trace-modes over one parser:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/operator-guide.md-25-> - `--trace-mode router` (default for `run()` / CI) — deterministic router-replay over the real playbook prompts, scored against the playbook's expected-ref gold (replaces the old empty-gold fixtures).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/operator-guide.md:26:> - `--trace-mode live` — real `cli-opencode` dispatch; routing/advisor scenarios are run as routing-analysis prompts (the model states its routing as JSON, graded vs gold + observed activation); browser scenarios (MR/CB) route to a `bdg` browser executor. Add `--d4` for the opt-in **D4-R task-outcome ablation** — the model is asked to *do* a routine task skill-on vs skill-off (a patch plan + verification, not a routing list), claude-graded into an advisory `D4_task_outcome` (the real usefulness measure, separate from the hallucination-grader D4). A↔B divergence + `assetRecall` are reported alongside.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/operator-guide.md:27:> - Flags: `--scenarios <ids|critical>`, `--executor`, `--playbook-dir`. Live model via env `SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_MODEL` / `SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_VARIANT`.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/operator-guide.md:28:> - **Live model guidance:** `gpt-5.5-fast --variant high` completes (~78s); `xhigh` is too slow and times out. Live is advisory (cost + nondeterminism) — the gated verdict stays driven by router mode + the D5 hard gate. Auto-CREATE generator (`playbook-generator.cjs`) is opt-in + staged.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/operator-guide.md-29-
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/operator-guide.md-30-## 2. INVOCATION
