.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/operator-guide.md-82-
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/operator-guide.md:83:D1-inter is **built and deterministic** but opt-in (`--advisor-mode=python`); the live in-situ trace (Mode B) is built. The weighted **D4** dimension stays `unscored-mode-a` on purpose — its grader scores *hallucination*, not task usefulness, so folding it would mislabel the number. Real usefulness is the opt-in **D4-R task-outcome ablation** (`--d4`), reported separately as advisory `D4_task_outcome`, never summed into the weighted score. Mode A stays honest about coverage: the aggregate normalizes over the dimensions actually measured.
