.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-skill-benchmark-presentation.txt-68-
.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-skill-benchmark-presentation.txt:69:- **D1-intra / D1-inter**: routing precision within the skill and advisor selection across skills (D1-inter is opt-in via `--advisor-mode=python`).
.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-skill-benchmark-presentation.txt-70-- **D2**: resource discovery and load efficiency.
.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-skill-benchmark-presentation.txt-71-- **D3**: over-routing detection.
.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-skill-benchmark-presentation.txt-72-- **D4**: usefulness ablation (opt-in, approximate).
.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-skill-benchmark-presentation.txt-73-- **D5**: structural hard gate (must pass; blocks a clean verdict when it fails).
.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-skill-benchmark-presentation.txt-74-
.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-skill-benchmark-presentation.txt:75:Mode A (router-replay) scores D1-intra, D2, D3, D5 deterministically. Mode B (live playbook) dispatches a skill's own `manual_testing_playbook` corpus through `cli-opencode`; it is advisory, and the gated verdict stays router mode plus the D5 hard gate.
