codex
Two implementation-spec gaps are now concrete. First, Lane C’s existing stability guard fingerprints the hub’s local `leaf-manifest.json`, while the compiled resolver serves from the separate activation manifest; a concurrent re-mint or flip can mix serving generations within one report. Second, archived reports persist absolute worktree paths, so the current “provenance” survives relocation only as an unchecked string.
codex
The first durable compiled-vs-legacy Lane C result needs a run-atomic serving snapshot, portable provenance, and a complete command path. The planned parity module is the right boundary; the frozen replay, scorer, and loader stay untouched.

1. **P0 — make parity runs atomic against serving state.** Lane C currently snapshots only `<hub>/leaf-manifest.json` before/after a run, while compiled serving is gated by the separate activation manifest. A re-mint or serving flip can therefore mix generations inside one report. Capture activation-manifest bytes/digest, selected policy hash, generation, authority, and fence before the first compiled child call; re-read after the last call; abort with `serving_state_changed_during_run` on any difference. The compiled response already exposes policy hash and generation. [run-skill-benchmark.cjs:99](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:99), [run-skill-benchmark.cjs:282](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:282), [resolve.cjs:19](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs:19), [compiled-route.cjs:77](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/compiled-route.cjs:77)

2. **P1 — archive portable, verifiable provenance rather than an absolute worktree path.** The scorer writes the resolved absolute target root into every report, and the existing `sk-code` archive already points at another workspace location. The renderer accepts any non-empty string as provenance. Add an orchestrator-owned `compiledRouting.provenance` block with repo-relative hub root, activation-manifest digest/path, selected-policy tuple, front-door path digest, frozen-file hashes, and source revision; render it from JSON. This requires no scorer edit. [score-skill-benchmark.cjs:1791](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/score-skill-benchmark.cjs:1791), [router-final report:7](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/router-final/skill-benchmark-report.json:7), [build-report.cjs:46](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/build-report.cjs:46)

3. **P1 — wire the supported command envelope if the recommended parity mode flag remains.** The benchmark spec recommends `--compiled-routing-parity on|off|auto`, but `loop-host` forwards only its allowlisted options, and both command workflows bind and dispatch only the current inputs. Add the option to the host allowlist, command input gate, presentation contract, and both YAML workflows; otherwise omit the option entirely and make the report record the fixed resolved `auto` behavior. [014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:242](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:242), [loop-host.cjs:73](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs:73), [loop-host.cjs:198](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs:198), [deep-skill-benchmark-auto.yaml:30](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-skill-benchmark-auto.yaml:30)

The production sequence is: land P0 status/front-door and P3 eligibility interfaces; add the parity adapter around the frozen modules; run a fresh `sk-code/benchmark/compiled-parity-router/` router-mode sibling; write both report files from the JSON; then update the benchmark index. The storage contract requires sibling run labels and forbids regenerating `baseline/`. This deterministic artifact proves parity only; the required LUNA HIGH playbook evidence remains a separate live/manual gate. [014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:99](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:99), [skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md:36](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md:36), [skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md:89](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md:89), [014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:83](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:83)

